(42, 13, 1, 26, 9, 5, 7, 'whose blood Pilate had mingled', 'Violence and Judgment Themes', 'This connection highlights the theme of violence and divine judgment present in both passages. In Luke, the mingling of blood signifies a brutal act, while Ezekiel describes a command to slay without pity, emphasizing the severity of judgment.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
