(42, 13, 2, 18, 22, 5, 16, 'suffered such things', 'Connection of Suffering and Sin', 'Both passages emphasize the relationship between suffering and perceived sinfulness. In Luke, Jesus questions the assumption that suffering indicates greater sin, while Job discusses the consequences of wickedness and iniquities.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
